From 83e3beb11417b3e9bac1d6593cc51dac7beb6a8b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 10:06:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix pop/crack, add amp attack, restructure UI into
 Attack/Body/Shape columns
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Pop/crack fix:
- Revert osc.reset() to phase=0 (zero-crossing). Phase=0.25 caused an
  instantaneous jump to full amplitude on the first sample — a textbook click.
- Add onset ramp: every fire() captures amp_attack_ms as onset_total samples.
  The amplitude is multiplied by a linear 0→1 ramp over that window before
  reaching the limiter. Default 2ms is inaudible but eliminates the click at
  any drive setting.

New amp_attack param (0–20ms, default 2ms) exposed as the "Atk" knob in
the ATTACK panel. Users can tighten it to 0 for a drum-machine snap or
extend it for a soft, swelling onset.

UI restructured into two rows of three semantic columns:
  Row 1: ATTACK (click + onset) | BODY (pitch sweep + amp decay) | SHAPE (distortion routing)
  Row 2: EQ/SCREECH (pre-dist) | OUTPUT (limiter + OS) | SEQ (BPM)

SHAPE panel now labels its scope: "[high band only]" — distortion is
applied only above the crossover frequency; the sub band always stays
clean. EQ panel labels "[pre-dist]" so the screech-generation routing is
visually obvious without reading the docs.

ui.columns() replaces the old horizontal_top panels so each column fills
its natural share of the window width. ScrollArea wraps everything so
the window can be resized smaller without clipping content.

Presets updated: all six presets tuned to the triode shaper's actual
response curve, with correct amp_attack values. Sub Pressure now uses
bias=0 (symmetric triode) to stay clean; Raw Screech and Fold Metal
verified to not click.

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
